# scan-secrets.allowlist - exact full lines to ignore (grep -Fx match)
# Each entry is the scanner output line WITHOUT the leading "[secret] "
# prefix, i.e. the literal "file:line:content" form. Line numbers are
# part of the match, so an entry stops matching if the line moves - the
# scanner then re-flags rather than silently passing, which is fail-safe.
# Add narrow entries with a comment above explaining why.

# Scanner self-reference: the literal pattern in its own source.
.claude/scripts/scan-secrets.sh:36:  'service_role'

# Skill doc documenting which patterns the scanner matches (not a secret).
.claude/skills/secret-scanning/SKILL.md:37:| `service_role`                                          | Supabase service-role key    |
.claude/skills/secret-scanning/SKILL.md:41:| `(password\|secret\|api_key\|service_role)=['"]...['"]` | Inline secret literal        |
